[wait time="2.0"]
gabbie: [i]I take a deep breath. Here goes nothing.[/i]
gabbie: You are my greatest love. My shining star. My constant. The Polaris of my evening sky.
gabbie: [i]My eyes are warm. I can barely make out my handwritten notes.[/i]
gabbie: [i]I can’t meet her gaze either as I say these things, but I have to push through.[/i]
gabbie: I take you to be my wedded wife. To have and to hold from this day forward…
gabbie: [i]Almost there.[/i]
gabbie: For better, for worse, for richer, for poorer, in sickness and in health, to love and to cherish… till death we do part.
gabbie: [i]Finally…[/i]
gabbie: I love you so much, Tabu.
gabbie: [i]The woman in front of me, my future wife, stands completely still. Why isn’t she saying anythi-[/i]
tala: HAHAHAHAHAHAHAH
gabbie: Oh my goodness! Ta-
tala: HAHAHAHAHAHHAHAHAHA
tala: HAHAHAHAHAHAHAH
gabbie: [i]That’s it. I instinctively cover my face with my hands, letting my written vows drift away to who knows where.[/i]
gabbie: [i]My fiance’s laugh is infectious, and we end up laughing until we’re both sprawled across the floor.[/i]
gabbie: [i]Eventually, she wipes the tears off her face and turns to me.[/i]
tala: Tabu? Are you seriously going with that, Gabbie?
